prise. The enterprise is not registered for the auxiliary NACE activity at the State Statistical Office. These data have been prepared by the Ministry of Economy“. 3) f) Largest enterprises: "The symbol ** next to the figures for gross output and number of employed indicates that the data is for 2002. Data for 2003 do not exist. Included are enterprises which are important for the presented NACE activity.“ 3) f) Largest enterprises: "Enterprises with less than 10 employees were not considered.„. 3) h) Productivity per employee: "In the Republic of Macedonia, there are not available data for hours worked. Because of this, it is not possible to calculate productivity per hour worked. Productivity per employee is calculated as a ratio between the Gross value added and the number of employees„. 
